Well. drink up...

1036
01:03:18.533 --> 01:03:20.753
so. we can all clean up
this mess you made

1037
01:03:20.927 --> 01:03:24.235
before the Yakuza turn up
and kill every single one of us.

1038
01:03:24.409 --> 01:03:25.627
You. too. huh?

1039
01:03:26.367 --> 01:03:28.805
Just doing what I need to
to survive.

1040
01:03:28.979 --> 01:03:30.328
At what cost?

1041
01:03:31.590 --> 01:03:33.244
My soul.

1042
01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.377
Although.
they're cheap nowadays.

1043
01:03:36.551 --> 01:03:38.510
Hell. you sold yours.
didn't you?

1044
01:03:39.380 --> 01:03:40.904
I didn't sell mine.

1045
01:03:42.906 --> 01:03:44.037
I lost it.

1046
01:03:46.431 --> 01:03:47.562
How did you know?

1047
01:03:47.736 --> 01:03:49.608
Bartenders hear
a lot of bullshit.

1048
01:03:51.784 --> 01:03:54.221
You get really good
at sniffing out the lies.

1049
01:03:55.875 --> 01:04:00.053
Your story was true right
until the end. am I right?

1050
01:04:04.275 --> 01:04:06.190
The girl didn't kill her dad.

1051
01:04:07.844 --> 01:04:08.888
You did.

1052
01:04:14.676 --> 01:04:15.852
I shot him...

1053
01:04:18.028 --> 01:04:20.682
right between the eyes
for what he'd done.

1054
01:04:24.991 --> 01:04:26.471
I figured it was justice.

1055
01:04:28.777 --> 01:04:30.301
Now. I don't know.

1056
01:04:31.302 --> 01:04:34.000
I've been avoiding making
any choices since then.

1057
01:04:35.001 --> 01:04:38.135
just watching life
from the sidelines.

1058
01:04:38.831 --> 01:04:40.398
That's my truth.

1059
01:04:41.442 --> 01:04:44.532
Now. you go.
What happened to Gunderson?

1060
01:04:44.706 --> 01:04:46.099
I already told mine.

1061
01:04:46.273 --> 01:04:47.666
Me. fish? Fuck no.

1062
01:04:48.623 --> 01:04:50.234
Probably the only one
in town who don't.

1063
01:04:51.844 --> 01:04:54.325
Gunderson. he had
a fishing pole in one hand.

1064
01:04:54.499 --> 01:04:57.284
like this one.
and an auger in the other.

1065
01:04:57.937 --> 01:05:00.244
So. my guess is he thought
he was going ice fishing.

1066
01:05:01.201 --> 01:05:03.464
Who the fuck goes
ice fishing with a fly rod?

1067
01:05:03.638 --> 01:05:05.118
No one.

1068
01:05:06.815 --> 01:05:09.079
I lied. I killed him.

1069
01:05:09.688 --> 01:05:11.690
Because he wanted
a bigger cut of the deal?

1070
01:05:11.864 --> 01:05:15.215
Because he wanted out
of the job. of...

1071
01:05:15.389 --> 01:05:18.958
...the town. the arrangement.

1072
01:05:19.306 --> 01:05:20.307
Why?

1073
01:05:22.048 --> 01:05:23.180
Missed his kid.

1074
01:05:24.094 --> 01:05:25.834
This town made him choose.

1075
01:05:26.705 --> 01:05:29.534
It's a small town
in every way. you know.

1076
01:05:30.230 --> 01:05:33.016
- small-minded.
- Yeah. I get that.

1077
01:05:34.713 --> 01:05:37.759
- And no one gets out.
- Not even him.

1078
01:05:39.196 --> 01:05:40.980
So. you got him drunk and...

1079
01:05:42.547 --> 01:05:43.809
walked him out and...

1080
01:05:43.983 --> 01:05:45.724
Watched him freeze to death...

1081
01:05:46.943 --> 01:05:50.163
which takes longer
than you'd think.

1082
01:05:50.903 --> 01:05:54.733
Unless you're wet. which he was.
because I poured water on him.

1083
01:05:55.995 --> 01:05:58.084
But I learned something
about myself that night.

1084
01:05:59.346 --> 01:06:01.087
What's that?

1085
01:06:01.261 --> 01:06:02.915
That I can do
what needs to be done.

1086
01:06:04.177 --> 01:06:07.224
- What happened to you?
- Nothing I didn't choose.

1087
01:06:10.009 --> 01:06:11.968
Like I said.
that's a cool belt.

1088
01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:21.586
What the fuck. Sheriff?

1089
01:06:22.804 --> 01:06:23.936
Tell me about it.

1090
01:06:25.851 --> 01:06:27.940
I think he would have
wanted you to have this.

1091
01:06:28.114 --> 01:06:30.073
especially in light
of current events.

1092
01:06:35.252 --> 01:06:36.993
Let's go. Deputy.

1093
01:06:37.950 --> 01:06:40.257
This shit storm
is only gonna get worse.

1094
01:06:53.183 --> 01:06:54.140
Whoa!

1095
01:07:00.451 --> 01:07:01.539
Hey. Blaine.

1096
01:07:02.801 --> 01:07:04.629
Light 'em up!

1097
01:07:08.067 --> 01:07:09.416
Bulletproof. motherfuckers.

1098
01:07:17.598 --> 01:07:18.469
Whoa!

1099
01:07:23.822 --> 01:07:25.780
Hey. Blaine!

1100
01:07:27.652 --> 01:07:29.523
- Yeah. Joe?
- Damn it.

1101
01:07:30.176 --> 01:07:32.265
Did we leave anyone
back at the bank?

1102
01:07:33.571 --> 01:07:34.615
No. Joe.

1103
01:07:35.877 --> 01:07:36.965
And the vault?

1104
01:07:37.879 --> 01:07:39.011
Yeah. Joe?

1105
01:07:40.491 --> 01:07:43.668
Is it... still open?

1106
01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:13.306
Yoo-hoo!

1107
01:08:13.480 --> 01:08:14.916
Answer the phone.

1108
01:08:16.918 --> 01:08:21.532
My deputy is currently securing
the contents of your vault.

1109
01:08:27.494 --> 01:08:28.539
Securing?

1110
01:08:29.279 --> 01:08:32.282
Bricks of C4
have been planted

1111
01:08:32.586 --> 01:08:37.374
in and amongst the Yakuza's
physical deposits. as it were.

1112
01:08:39.419 --> 01:08:44.381
So. to sum up.
if I die. it all goes boom.

1113
01:08:44.903 --> 01:08:46.426
And if it goes boom.

1114
01:08:46.600 --> 01:08:49.995
well. them being
the Yakuza and all.

1115
01:08:50.735 --> 01:08:52.911
I don't think it ends
real well for you.

1116
01:08:54.042 --> 01:08:56.219
If we don't finish this
here and now.

1117
01:08:56.393 --> 01:08:57.611
the Yakuza will hunt down

1118
01:08:57.785 --> 01:09:00.353
and kill each
and every one of us.

1119
01:09:01.137 --> 01:09:02.486
me included.

1120
01:09:04.575 --> 01:09:06.490
But wait. there's more.

1121
01:09:08.579 --> 01:09:09.928
I've got a proposal.

1122
01:09:13.105 --> 01:09:14.802
We tidy up the bank.

1123
01:09:14.976 --> 01:09:18.415
make it look like an accident.
like nothing bad happened.

1124
01:09:19.590 --> 01:09:22.158
Just another Saturday.

1125
01:09:23.246 --> 01:09:24.203
Mm.

1126
01:09:24.943 --> 01:09:28.294
Kenny. you say this
is Belgian chocolate?

1127
01:09:28.468 --> 01:09:29.600
French.

1128
01:09:29.774 --> 01:09:32.516
Mm. Same difference. you know.

1129
01:09:34.735 --> 01:09:37.129
So. that's your plan?

1130
01:09:38.086 --> 01:09:39.087
That's it.

1131
01:09:41.046 --> 01:09:42.656
Just make it seem like
any other day.

1132
01:09:42.830 --> 01:09:44.092
Basically. yeah.

1133
01:09:45.137 --> 01:09:49.185
The Yakuza show up.
their treasure is untouched.

1134
01:09:49.707 --> 01:09:52.666
Nothing more than a car accident
that set off the alarm.

1135
01:09:52.840 --> 01:09:55.626
Life in Normal is normal. calm.

1136
01:09:57.105 --> 01:10:00.413
Calm... cleans messy.

1137
01:10:01.153 --> 01:10:02.285
That's right.

1138
01:10:03.242 --> 01:10:07.812
Why don't I just kill you
right now?

1139
01:10:10.206 --> 01:10:12.295
The only thing your boss
is gonna give a shit about

1140
01:10:12.469 --> 01:10:13.774
is that you messed up.

1141
01:10:15.385 --> 01:10:18.214
I say we play the hand
that's been dealt to all of us.

1142
01:10:19.693 --> 01:10:23.001
You make us look good.
we'll make you look good.

1143
01:10:24.089 --> 01:10:25.482
And maybe you get to keep
the rest

1144
01:10:25.656 --> 01:10:27.223
of your goddamn fingers.

1145
01:10:31.531 --> 01:10:35.405
I'm sorry that I.
uh... killed your mayor.

1146
01:10:35.883 --> 01:10:37.494
I know you liked him a lot.

1147
01:10:38.799 --> 01:10:41.062
Though. he did seem
a bit of an a-hole.

1148
01:10:44.675 --> 01:10:45.632
Okay.

1149
01:10:47.373 --> 01:10:48.809
What do you say?

1150
01:10:50.246 --> 01:10:54.380
Well. it...
isn't much of a plan.

1151
01:10:54.902 --> 01:10:59.255
Well. I'm not much of a sheriff.
but I'm all you've got.

1152
01:11:06.131 --> 01:11:08.525
Hey. Alex.

1153
01:11:09.177 --> 01:11:10.396
Let's a put on a show.

1154
01:11:11.658 --> 01:11:13.530
I'm kind of liking...

1155
01:11:14.966 --> 01:11:15.967
Deputy.

1156
01:11:22.016 --> 01:11:22.974
Fuck yeah.

1157
01:11:24.802 --> 01:11:26.717
Come on. people!
This is the new Normal!

1158
01:11:26.891 --> 01:11:28.632
It's gotta seem
like an accident!

1159
01:11:28.806 --> 01:11:31.199
Like there wasn't
a massacre here. you know?

1160
01:11:31.374 --> 01:11:33.245
Bring it in! Bring it in!

1161
01:11:34.072 --> 01:11:35.726
Look for loose limbs!

1162
01:11:36.727 --> 01:11:38.859
Watch for blood splotches.

1163
01:11:39.730 --> 01:11:40.905
Cover 'em up.

1164
01:11:42.036 --> 01:11:45.083
Winter wonderland!
Let's go for it. folks.

1165
01:11:45.779 --> 01:11:47.912
Make it nice for our guests.

1166
01:11:48.913 --> 01:11:50.044
Let's bring it around.

1167
01:11:50.654 --> 01:11:54.266
Down there.
look for any loose entrails.

1168
01:12:18.203 --> 01:12:19.422
Swear to God.

1169
01:12:19.596 --> 01:12:22.990
I had no idea
about killing Gunderson.

1170
01:12:23.164 --> 01:12:24.470
You believed
that bullshit

1171
01:12:24.644 --> 01:12:26.037
about the fishing rod?

1172
01:12:26.211 --> 01:12:27.778
Sorry.
I'm not much of a fisherman.

1173
01:12:27.952 --> 01:12:29.345
but. yeah. I get your point.

1174
01:12:29.649 --> 01:12:31.912
And you tried to shoot me.

1175
01:12:32.086 --> 01:12:34.611
Yeah. I did shoot you.
but I didn't kill you.

1176
01:12:34.785 --> 01:12:36.656
That's the important thing.

1177
01:12:37.222 --> 01:12:39.311
We're here together.
both of us...

1178
01:12:41.444 --> 01:12:42.445
alive.

1179
01:12:44.751 --> 01:12:45.839
Do you. uh...

1180
01:12:46.362 --> 01:12:48.146
Do you really think
this is gonna work?

1181
01:12:50.453 --> 01:12:51.715
You a betting man?

1182
01:12:52.672 --> 01:12:54.457
To my own detriment.
to be sure.

1183
01:12:57.111 --> 01:13:00.158
I'd put a Benji on the lay.

1184
01:13:01.681 --> 01:13:04.162
Wait a minute. You're...
You're betting against us?

1185
01:13:08.166 --> 01:13:10.255
Oof. We're fucked. huh?

1186
01:13:11.822 --> 01:13:14.390
Well. best get into character.

1187
01:13:27.838 --> 01:13:30.014
You got some
explaining to do. don't you?

1188
01:13:30.188 --> 01:13:33.191
Yes. I have several
explanations.

1189
01:13:33.365 --> 01:13:36.934
As you can s...
Can you... Can you translate?

1190
01:13:38.892 --> 01:13:42.069
As you can see. the storm here
was something else.

1191
01:13:42.243 --> 01:13:45.508
It knocked out phones.
internet. cell service. hell.

1192
01:13:45.682 --> 01:13:47.379
you name it. it's down.

1193
01:13:47.553 --> 01:13:49.120
Howdy. y'all.

1194
01:13:50.251 --> 01:13:53.124
Oh. he's the interim.
like I told you.

1195
01:13:53.298 --> 01:13:56.562
He don't know shit.
He's. uh. not too bright.

1196
01:13:56.736 --> 01:13:58.216
Deputy Blaine.
you know these folks?

1197
01:13:58.390 --> 01:13:59.913
You want to explain to them
they can't come

1198
01:14:00.087 --> 01:14:02.089
tearing through our county
in a convoy like this

1199
01:14:02.263 --> 01:14:04.744
without getting
a greeting from the law?

1200
01:14:04.918 --> 01:14:07.878
Well. uh. this is actually
Pastor Oyabun. Sheriff.

1201
01:14:08.052 --> 01:14:09.662
- Oh. a pastor.
- Mm-hmm.

1202
01:14:09.836 --> 01:14:11.142
He's got a small parish

1203
01:14:11.316 --> 01:14:13.057
just over yonder
down near Everton.

1204
01:14:13.231 --> 01:14:15.102
What's his denomination?

1205
01:14:15.842 --> 01:14:18.062
Protestant. Ain't that right?

1206
01:14:18.454 --> 01:14:20.586
I don't know what the hell
you guys are talking about!

1207
01:14:20.760 --> 01:14:22.109
- Tell him.
- He's mad.

1208
01:14:22.283 --> 01:14:23.502
We must get going.

1209
01:14:23.676 --> 01:14:25.199
What's he upset about?

1210
01:14:25.504 --> 01:14:26.810
- Bank! Bank!
- I think...

1211
01:14:26.984 --> 01:14:28.899
I think that he wants to go
to the bank.

1212
01:14:29.073 --> 01:14:30.727
Are we going now or what?

1213
01:14:30.901 --> 01:14:32.250
He can't go
to the bank. We've got the...

1214
01:14:32.424 --> 01:14:34.382
- Yeah. yeah. but...
- There's people down.

1215
01:14:34.557 --> 01:14:35.993
- It's true that...
- Hey!

1216
01:14:36.167 --> 01:14:37.690
Hey. hey.

1217
01:14:37.864 --> 01:14:40.171
- We'll make an exception.
- Make an exception.

1218
01:14:40.345 --> 01:14:43.043
- We'll give you an escort.
- Follow us. Let's go.

1219
01:14:43.217 --> 01:14:44.741
Let's go. hurry up.

1220
01:14:44.915 --> 01:14:46.394
You start driving.

1221
01:14:46.569 --> 01:14:48.484
Okay. Deputy Blaine.

1222
01:14:48.658 --> 01:14:51.269
let's take our guests
the long way around.

1223
01:14:52.139 --> 01:14:54.490
Give them a little more time
to fix up the bank.

1224
01:14:56.796 --> 01:14:58.581
How can these assholes

1225
01:14:58.755 --> 01:15:00.713
get lost on a straight road?

1226
01:15:02.454 --> 01:15:03.586
Those aren't
the best shoes.

1227
01:15:03.760 --> 01:15:05.109
Yes. sir.
Right this way.

1228
01:15:05.283 --> 01:15:06.414
So. just watch
your step. Come on.

1229
01:15:06.589 --> 01:15:08.112
This is it?

1230
01:15:08.286 --> 01:15:08.678
Well. it doesn't look good.

1231
01:15:08.852 --> 01:15:10.244
I know.

1232
01:15:10.418 --> 01:15:11.811
My money better be safe.

1233
01:15:11.985 --> 01:15:12.551
Careful of the snow.

1234
01:15:19.602 --> 01:15:21.168
The driver was killed on impact.

1235
01:15:21.342 --> 01:15:22.909
as was the bank manager
and security guard.

1236
01:15:23.083 --> 01:15:24.302
- Where's Haru?
- Killed.

1237
01:15:24.476 --> 01:15:26.043
And the vault?

1238
01:15:26.217 --> 01:15:27.827
Sheriff. you mind
if I show him the vault?

1239
01:15:28.001 --> 01:15:30.395
The church has some papers
in their safe deposit box.

1240
01:15:30.569 --> 01:15:33.137
- Yeah. sure. go ahead.
- Good. Yeah. this way.

1241
01:15:34.181 --> 01:15:35.966
The building's in fine shape.

1242
01:15:36.140 --> 01:15:38.359
Uh. actually. it wasn't
a load-bearing wall.

1243
01:15:38.534 --> 01:15:39.970
Excuse me. Uh...

1244
01:15:40.144 --> 01:15:44.191
As you can see.
the vault. it's untouched.

1245
01:15:44.365 --> 01:15:46.672
Excuse me. Pristine.

1246
01:15:46.846 --> 01:15:49.153
Whoa! The church
has done well. huh?

1247
01:15:54.158 --> 01:15:55.855
Pretty color. huh?

1248
01:15:56.029 --> 01:15:57.378
Now. who's hungry?

1249
01:16:08.564 --> 01:16:10.478
Why did you invite
them out for food?

1250
01:16:12.568 --> 01:16:15.309
I only know. like. four phrases
in Japanese. and...

1251
01:16:16.441 --> 01:16:17.616
I guess I panicked.

1252
01:16:21.185 --> 01:16:23.143
Is your boss
enjoying the meatloaf?

1253
01:16:25.842 --> 01:16:28.018
This is divine.

1254
01:16:30.237 --> 01:16:31.804
Your English is very good. sir.

1255
01:16:32.762 --> 01:16:34.154
I watch a lot of Friends.

1256
01:16:34.546 --> 01:16:36.287
Who's in for mimosas?

1257
01:16:36.461 --> 01:16:39.377
Should I make a toast?

1258
01:16:40.813 --> 01:16:43.642
- Don't.
- Uh. excuse me. Um...

1259
01:16:45.905 --> 01:16:49.343
I. uh...
I'd like to propose a toast.

1260
01:16:49.517 --> 01:16:51.607
Um... You know. I'm. uh.

1261
01:16:51.781 --> 01:16:54.610
what you might call
a "people person."

1262
01:16:54.784 --> 01:16:57.874
So. this toast is to friendship.
I think it's important

1263
01:16:58.048 --> 01:16:59.745
that I take credit
for this event.

1264
01:16:59.919 --> 01:17:02.182
When I become
the next sheriff of Normal.

1265
01:17:02.356 --> 01:17:06.056
there will be many more
opportunities to come together

1266
01:17:06.230 --> 01:17:09.625
and break bread.
strengthening our link.

1267
01:17:09.799 --> 01:17:14.630
And with Pastor Oyabun
and his friendly. friendly.

1268
01:17:14.804 --> 01:17:19.417
um. congregation.
I think this is a new chapter

1269
01:17:19.591 --> 01:17:22.812
for our town
and our happy arrangement.

1270
01:17:22.986 --> 01:17:26.903
So. I'd like to say
thank you for all your help

1271
01:17:27.077 --> 01:17:31.298
and to many.
many more years

1272
01:17:31.472 --> 01:17:38.088
of friendly people helping
other friendly people.

1273
01:17:53.930 --> 01:17:54.887
Please!

1274
01:17:58.804 --> 01:17:59.892
Oh. shit.

1275
01:18:44.458 --> 01:18:45.503
Asshole!

1276
01:18:48.898 --> 01:18:50.290
Hey!
Get your hands off!

1277
01:20:51.020 --> 01:20:53.413
God damn it!

1278
01:21:32.539 --> 01:21:34.106
Sheriff?

1279
01:21:35.586 --> 01:21:36.674
Sheriff!

1280
01:21:44.334 --> 01:21:46.684
All friends now?

1281
01:21:53.996 --> 01:21:55.823
Anyone for pie?

1282
01:22:17.628 --> 01:22:18.629
Mm.

1283
01:22:26.811 --> 01:22:29.901
You want to be
sheriff now?

1284
01:22:33.035 --> 01:22:34.775
Yeah. Yeah. sure.

1285
01:22:42.566 --> 01:22:44.481
Thanks for taking care of it
for me.

1286
01:22:45.917 --> 01:22:50.313
Oh. There's one other thing.

1287
01:22:52.576 --> 01:22:56.058
Here's that 100 on the lay.
Guess you won.

1288
01:22:58.582 --> 01:23:00.062
Can I have that pie back?

1289
01:23:17.949 --> 01:23:19.777
This is Penny.
I'm sorry I missed you.

1290
01:23:19.951 --> 01:23:21.474
Please leave a message.

1291
01:23:21.648 --> 01:23:22.998
and I'll circle back
when I can. Thanks.

1292
01:23:23.172 --> 01:23:25.435
Hey. Penny. it's me.

1293
01:23:25.609 --> 01:23:28.351
I'm... I'm in Texas now.

1294
01:23:28.525 --> 01:23:32.007
Yeah. filling in for a sheriff
on maternity leave.

1295
01:23:32.181 --> 01:23:36.141
I much prefer the weather here.
It's warm. Don't miss the cold.

1296
01:23:36.315 --> 01:23:40.232
Oh. and I picked up an
interim deputy along the way.

1297
01:23:40.406 --> 01:23:42.278
People are pretty much
the same.

1298
01:23:42.452 --> 01:23:44.323
Then. again. not.

1299
01:23:44.497 --> 01:23:45.846
All things considered. though...

1300
01:23:46.021 --> 01:23:49.633
...I'm in a better place.

1301
01:23:49.807 --> 01:23:52.201
As for the town of Normal.
well.

1302
01:23:52.375 --> 01:23:54.855
I left it as I found it.
you could say.

1303
01:23:56.379 --> 01:23:58.163
I mean. that's the job.
isn't it?

1304
01:23:59.164 --> 01:24:01.514
Besides. I'm never looking
for trouble.

1305
01:24:02.080 --> 01:24:04.952
If it wants you.
it'll find you on its own.

1306
01:24:05.823 --> 01:24:08.782
and it can be hard
to shake once it does.

1307
01:24:12.090 --> 01:24:15.093
Well. thanks for listening.
Penny. I...

1308
01:24:15.920 --> 01:24:17.095
Hi. Ulysses.

1309
01:24:18.140 --> 01:24:19.663
Hey. Penny.

